                  <summary change="#add-summary">
                     1 copy of Kitāb-i Sharḥ al-vāṣilīn va tawsīf al-jāhilīn by Jamālī Ardistānī
                  </summary>
                  <msItem xml:id="Or_12999-item1">
                     <author ref="hhttp://viaf.org/viaf/68058549" key="person_68058549">
                        <persName xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="standard">Jamālī Ardistānī</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="fa">جمالی اردستانی</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_8129">Kitāb-i Sharḥ al-vāṣilīn va tawsīf al-jāhilīn</title>
                     <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_8129">کتاب شرح الواصلین و توصیف الجاهلین</title>
                     <note>This is said by Ivanow (ASB, No. 648) to be the seventh part of a large mas̲navī entitled <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Bayān-i Ḥaqā’iq-i Aḥvāl-i Sayyid al-Mursalīn <foreign xml:lang="fa">بیان حقائق احوال سید لمرسلین</foreign>
                        </title> by Jamālī-i Ardistānī, but in <ref target="#Uk_or_11946">Or. 11946</ref> the seventh part is the <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Kashf al-Arvāḥ <foreign xml:lang="fa">کشف الارواح</foreign>
                        </title>. The latter is not the introduction to the Bayān, as suggested by Ivanow, but its concluding section. Hence the Sharḥ al-vāṣilīn must be an entirely separate work by Jamālī</note>
                     <listBibl>
                        <bibl>For a more detailed description see Meredith-Owens 1968, page 76.</bibl>
                     </listBibl>
                     <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                  </msItem>
